=  The <span style="color: #000000;">**Center Party**</span> and the Reichbanner
  
Since the founding of the Reichbanner in 1926, it has mostly been dominated by politicians from the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span>, with a bulk of its membership being <span style="color: #c00000;">socialist</span> workers.
However, with the fear of the Reichbanner "diluting religious fervour" and the strong disapproval from the clerics, the reaction of the <span style="color: #000000;">**Center**</span> has been lukewarm to say the least. Despite nominal membership from ccentrists like Marx and Kohler, enthusiasm for the Reichbanner exists solely amidst ardent republicans such as Joos or Wirth. 
In light of the increasingly volatile political landscape and rise of the miltant <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**SA**</span>, there has been growing pressure from the left of the party of officially affiliate the <span style="color: #000000;">**Center**</span> with the Reichabnner.
However, our socially heterogeneous base might not take kindly to such cooperation with the <span style="color: #c00000;">socialists</span>. Now, as German democracy is under siege, how will we respond to the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span>'s overtures?

- @endorse: The <span style="color: #000000;">**Center**</span> officially affliates itself with the Reichbanner.
- @reject: Surprisingly, we have rejected the overtures from the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span>.

@endorse
