@reject
view-if: z_party_leader = "Kaas"
on-arrival: pro_republic -= 5; spd_left += 1; spd_relation -= 5; ddp_relation -= 3; left_dissent += 5; left_labor_dissent += 3; z_workers -= 3; z_new_middle -= 2; nsdap_workers += 3; nsdap_catholics += 1; endorse_seen += 1; ddp_right += 1; rb_strength -= 300; 

Despite the our friendly relations with the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span>, our party has decided to rebuff the overtures of the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span>, with this direct repudiation of the Reichbanner causing some from our party to leave. While the Christian Left in the party question our commitment to the <span style="color: #000000;">We</span><span style="color: #DD0000;">im</span><span style="color: #FFCC00;">ar</span> system, the Windhorostbund is furious at our inactivity in the face of the growing strength of the <span style="color: #7A3C00;">**NSDAP**</span>.
Meanwhile, Catholic <span style="color: #3E88B3;">conservatives</span>are pleased with our commitment to being a party of the center, but others question how we have let cooperation with the <span style="color: #c00000;">**SPD**</span> come this far. 

 
